From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 08:32:10 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?[DOSKUTSU]=20dos:=20Phase=209=20wave=2016.2=20p?=
 =?UTF-8?q?atch=200029=20=E2=80=94=20banked-flush=20bank-1=20offset=20fix?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fix the missing-bottom-strip visual regression introduced by patch 0026's
8bpp mode pick (wave 16). On real HW Cirrus + UNIVBE 6.70 in 320×240×8bpp
banked mode (mode 0x01F8), the bottom ~35 scanlines of every frame
rendered as black despite BankedDosmemput logging "76,800 bytes / 2
switches per flush" — bytes were going somewhere not visible.

Diagnostic chain:
- Patch 0027 audit (wave 16): bank-1 readback at win_base+0 was zero on
  5/5 occurrences. Refuted H-A (display-start origin) and H-B (flush
  stops at bank 0); proved bank 1 in VRAM is genuinely empty after the
  production write.
- Patch 0028 sentinel (wave 16.1): explicit SwitchBank(1) +
  dosmemput(buf, 16, win_base) + SwitchBank(1) + dosmemget(win_base)
  match=1 on 5/5 flushes. Refuted H-C (bank-switch ineffective) and H-D
  (write/read window mismatch). The SwitchBank+dosmemput primitive
  itself works correctly; the bug is specifically in the production
  BankedDosmemput call's bank-1 dosmemput dst.

Original BankedDosmemput recomputed `bank = dst_offset / win_gran_bytes`
and `off_in_win = dst_offset % win_gran_bytes` afresh each loop
iteration. With dst_offset=65536 and win_gran_bytes=65536 in iter 2,
that's mathematically bank=1 and off_in_win=0 — correct on paper. But
the SDL_FORCE_INLINE expansion at the call site (line 929) produced a
bank-1 dosmemput that didn't reach VRAM bank 1 in practice. Symptom
matches: 76800 - 65536 = 11264 bytes / 320 bytes-per-line = 35.2
scanlines black, exactly the visible bottom-strip width.

Fix: explicit bank-and-off_in_win loop-carried locals, advanced by
`bank++; off_in_win = 0` at end of each iteration. Same byte count, same
two bank switches, just a defensive form that doesn't depend on
modular-arithmetic recomputation. Added one-shot WAVE16-2-BANK1-FIX
diagnostic on first non-bank-0 dosmemput so build-qa can grep the
binary's strings to verify the patch landed and the next real-HW iter's
SDLDBG.LOG positively confirms the per-call args.

Predicted outcome: no fps impact (same bytes, same switches); cloud bg
extends across all 240 scanlines; DOSVESA-FB-VRAM-BANK1 readback shows
real cloud-pixel data instead of zeros.

Refs: docs/PHASE9-WAVE-17-18-PLAN.md § 1.5; patches 0027 (audit), 0028
(sentinel).
---
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c | 70 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 66 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
index 6d60fc050..85d4e3d28 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
@@ -565,30 +565,92 @@ SDL_FORCE_INLINE void SwitchBank(int bank, int *current_bank, Uint32 win_func_pt
 
 // Copy a contiguous byte range from system RAM to VRAM through the banked
 // window, switching banks as needed.
+//
+// DOSKUTSU patch 0029 (wave 16.2): bank-1 dst-offset fix.
+//
+// Wave-16 visual regression: bottom ~35 scanlines render as black on real
+// HW Cirrus + UNIVBE 6.70 in 320×240×8bpp banked mode (mode 0x01F8). The
+// wave-16.1 sentinel test (patch 0028) proved that an explicit
+// SwitchBank(1) + dosmemput(buf, 16, win_base) + SwitchBank(1) +
+// dosmemget(win_base) round-trip works correctly (match=1) — so the
+// SwitchBank primitive itself is fine. But the wave-16 audit's bank-1
+// readback (also via SwitchBank(1) + dosmemget(win_base)) showed all-zero
+// 5/5 occurrences, meaning the production write into bank 1 didn't land
+// at win_base+0 as it should have. Bottom 11264 bytes of the framebuffer
+// (76800 - 65536 = 11264 B = 35.2 scanlines × 320 B/line) were going
+// somewhere else.
+//
+// The original implementation computed `off_in_win = dst_offset %
+// win_gran_bytes` and `bank = dst_offset / win_gran_bytes` afresh each
+// iteration. With dst_offset=65536 and win_gran_bytes=65536, that's
+// mathematically 0 and 1 respectively — correct on paper. But the
+// SDL_FORCE_INLINE expansion of this function at the call site (line 929)
+// produced bank-1 dosmemput writes that didn't reach VRAM bank 1 in
+// practice. The defensive rewrite here:
+//   1. Tracks `bank` and `off_in_win` as explicit loop-carried locals
+//      rather than recomputing modulo every iteration. After each bank is
+//      filled, `bank++` and `off_in_win = 0` reset cleanly.
+//   2. Adds a one-shot WAVE16-2-BANK1-FIX diagnostic on the first
+//      multi-bank flush so the next iter's SDLDBG.LOG confirms the math
+//      runtime: bank=1 src_off=65536 dst_off=0 bytes=11264 win_base=0xA0000.
+//
+// Same number of bytes (76800) and bank switches (2) per flush; pure
+// visual fix, no perf delta. Verification: post-fix DOSVESA-FB-VRAM-BANK1
+// readback should show real cloud-pixel data, not zeros.
 SDL_FORCE_INLINE void BankedDosmemput(const Uint8 *src, Uint32 total_bytes, Uint32 dst_offset,
                                       Uint32 win_gran_bytes, Uint32 win_size_bytes,
                                       Uint32 win_base, Uint32 win_func_ptr,
                                       int *current_bank)
 {
     Uint32 src_off = 0;
+    // DOS-PORT (wave 16.2): explicit bank index + per-bank offset, advanced
+    // by `bank++; off_in_win = 0` at end of each iteration. Avoids the
+    // `dst_offset / win_gran_bytes` and `dst_offset % win_gran_bytes`
+    // recomputation that wave-16.1 sentinel evidence suggests was silently
+    // miscompiling the bank-1 dosmemput dst.
+    int bank = (int)(dst_offset / win_gran_bytes);
+    Uint32 off_in_win = dst_offset - (Uint32)bank * win_gran_bytes;
     while (total_bytes > 0) {
-        int bank = (int)(dst_offset / win_gran_bytes);
-        Uint32 off_in_win = dst_offset % win_gran_bytes;
         Uint32 avail = win_size_bytes - off_in_win;
         Uint32 n = total_bytes;
         if (n > avail) {
             n = avail;
         }
         SwitchBank(bank, current_bank, win_func_ptr);
-        dosmemput(src + src_off, n, win_base + off_in_win);
+        const Uint32 dst_phys = win_base + off_in_win;
+        dosmemput(src + src_off, n, dst_phys);
+        // DOSKUTSU patch 0029 (wave 16.2 bank-1 offset fix) one-shot
+        // diagnostic: log the math the FIRST time we issue a non-bank-0
+        // dosmemput, so SDLDBG.LOG positively confirms src_off, dst_off,
+        // bytes, and win_base for the bank-1 (and any subsequent bank)
+        // write. Build-qa greps `strings build/doskutsu.exe` for
+        // "WAVE16-2-BANK1-FIX" to verify the fix landed in the binary.
+        {
+            static int _w162_logged = 0;
+            if (bank > 0 && _w162_logged == 0) {
+                _w162_logged = 1;
+                doskutsu_dbg_log(
+                    "WAVE16-2-BANK1-FIX: bank=%d src_off=%lu dst_off=%lu "
+                    "bytes=%lu win_base=0x%08lx win_gran=%lu win_size=%lu "
+                    "(first non-bank-0 dosmemput; defensive offset rewrite "
+                    "active)",
+                    bank, (unsigned long)src_off, (unsigned long)off_in_win,
+                    (unsigned long)n, (unsigned long)win_base,
+                    (unsigned long)win_gran_bytes, (unsigned long)win_size_bytes);
+            }
+        }
         // DOSKUTSU patch 0027 (wave 16 banked-flush audit): count
         // bytes pushed through the banked window. Used to confirm the
         // full fb_size lands per flush at 8bpp (76,800 B) vs falling
         // off after the first bank (would show ~65,536 B / flush).
         _dbg_bytes_written_total += n;
         src_off += n;
-        dst_offset += n;
         total_bytes -= n;
+        // DOS-PORT (wave 16.2): advance to next bank explicitly. The
+        // next iteration writes from offset 0 of the new bank, not
+        // dst_offset % win_gran_bytes of an accumulated dst_offset.
+        bank++;
+        off_in_win = 0;
     }
 }
 
